testTitle: Logic and Reasoning Sample Test I
questionText: A city is deciding where to locate a new community health centre that focuses on low-income residents. The ethical guidelines say the centre should (1) be within walking distance of the largest low-income neighbourhood, (2) not be next to a commercial alcohol district, and (3) prioritize areas with few existing clinics. Three candidate locations are proposed: Site A: in the middle of the largest low-income area, next to a street with many bars, with no clinic nearby. Site B: 15 minutes by bus from the largest low-income area, far from alcohol outlets, with one small clinic nearby. Site C: at the edge of the largest low-income area, not near alcohol outlets, with no clinic nearby. Which choice best follows the guidelines?
studentAnswers: ["Site C, because it balances proximity, safety, and lack of clinics"]
studentAnswersWithCorrectness: [{"value": "Site C, because it balances proximity, safety, and lack of clinics", "isCorrect": true}]
correctAnswers: ["Site C, because it balances proximity, safety, and lack of clinics"]
allChoices: {"Site A, because it is closest to the target population": false, "Site B, because it avoids alcohol outlets and competition": false, "Site C, because it balances proximity, safety, and lack of clinics": true, "None of the sites fit, so the project must be cancelled": false}
